Niger Governor Abubakar Sani-Bello is presiding over the Caretaker/Extra-ordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) at the party Secretariat in Abuja. As the time of filing the report, all the members of the committee are in attendance, including the Secretary of the Committee, Senator John James Akpanudoedehe. Sani-Bello, who arrived the party Secretariat around 12noon was , was ushered in by large crowd of party supporters and staff who hailed praised him as the new chairman. He then went straight to the National Working Committee (NWC) hall to await other members of the committee.   Gunmen kill two, injure others in Anambra filling station in…     Nigerians will not be used as mercenaries in Russia-Ukraine…     OAU student: Wife weeps, demands justice for late husband   On his trail was the Women representative in CECPC, Stella Okotete, the Youth Leader, Ismail Ahmed and Mr David Lyon. Also in attendance are Prof. Tahir Mamman, Senator Ali Abba, Sen. Ken Nnamani, Sen. Yusuf Yusuf Contacted, Sani Bello said: “We are only having our regular caretaker committee meeting. We are yet to take decision on anything The Nation gathered that some of the committee members had met in Senator Nanamani’s residence before coming to party headquarters for their meeting. Hon. Mai Mala Buni the chairman of the committee was absent.